The Compliance Model Governance Guide  is the strongest source for understanding the relationship among the Branch’s compliance systems. It identifies the Branch’s core compliance models as Transaction Monitoring, Filtering Program, and Customer Risk Rating. It also references supporting workbooks, model documentation, rule documentation, data mapping specifications, data dictionaries, data quality controls, reconciliation processes, system calibration, tuning, validation, and change management. The document indicates that Compliance, IT, Risk Management, Data Governance, and senior management all play roles in ensuring that systems are operating as designed and that changes are approved, tested, implemented, and documented. 
